# 2. 託された願い

Ena: Nope, not here.
Ena: (Mizuki... What are you doing right now?)
Ena: (I wonder if you're keeping in contact with someone else...)
Ena: (Or are you all alone...?)
Ena: (If Mizuki quits being a member of N25 and stops showing up in SEKAI...)
Ena: (We might never see each other again.)
Ena: But most of all...
Ena: I'm worried sick about you, Mizuki...
???: You're back again today.
Ena: Oh...
Ena: MEIKO...
Ena: Yeah, I was hoping that Mizuki would be here.
MEIKO: I see...
Ena: Have you seen Mizuki at all...?
MEIKO: No, I haven't...
MEIKO: I caught a glimpse of Mizuki's face a couple of times when I went over to see what was going on...
MEIKO: But I keep ending up somewhere pitch black. I think that phone's been put away in a drawer somewhere.
Ena: I see...
Ena: ...
Ena: Um, MEIKO?
Ena: Did you know this was gonna happen?
MEIKO: No.
MEIKO: I doubt anyone did.
MEIKO: However...
MEIKO: At the very least, I know that this isn't what Mizuki wanted.
Ena: Yeah, I agree.
Ena: (Mizuki just wanted to...)
Ena: To be with us like always.
Ena: We'd have pointless conversations, smile, laugh and just have fun together...
MEIKO: ...
Ena: But I...
Ena: After hearing the truth, I choked up... I didn't know what I should say.
MEIKO: Ena...
Ena: I keep asking myself.
Ena: What if I was more mentally prepared? What if Mizuki was the one who told me?
Ena: But...
Ena: I don't think that would've made a difference.
Ena: That time, if I just replied, “I didn't know that,” or, “Thanks for telling me.”
Ena: I mean, what happens when we try going back to our normal lives? We could talk online as N25 and go out shopping together...
Ena: But a part of me would always be wondering...
Ena: Can I ask? Should I ask? Would bringing it up hurt Mizuki in any way?
Ena: I wouldn't be able to get it out of my mind...
Ena: Which would be the worst thing for Mizuki...
MEIKO: ...
Ena: So, MEIKO, I have a question to ask you...
Ena: What if I asked for us to meet and talk once more?
Ena: What if I said that I still want us to be friends?
Ena: Is me just thinking that only going to hurt Mizuki even more...?
Ena: Because I honestly don't know...
MEIKO: Ena...
MEIKO: If you want to talk, you should talk.
MEIKO: Or rather...
MEIKO: I want you to say what's on your mind.
Ena: What...?
MEIKO: I'm also in the dark here.
MEIKO: No one knows the answer to this question. Actually, you probably won't find it anywhere...
Ena: ...
MEIKO: However, the person you're talking about is in a fragile state. One wrong move could cause an irreparable break.
MEIKO: In truth, I don't want anyone to take that risk.
MEIKO: But...
MEIKO: If we just let things proceed as is, then that's it.
MEIKO: That is why your feelings may be the last bastion of hope for Mizuki.
Ena: MEIKO...
Ena: Is it okay for me to...?
MEIKO: You should just do what you feel the need to do.
Ena: Yeah, I guess so...
Ena: Then, I'm going to meet with Mizuki.
Ena: We're going to meet and I'm going to say what's on my mind...
Ena: I'm going to say that I want us to keep being friends.
Ena: So, MEIKO, please let me know if you hear any news.
MEIKO: Okay, I will.
Ena: Thanks...
